  "time_ut": 1656305960,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf \u0d86\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dae\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0d85\u0dc0\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dba \u0db8\u0d9c\u0dc4\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dd4 \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd4 -IMF",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "US recession not easy to avoid -IMF",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The head of the International Monetary Fund (IMF) says there is a \"narrow path\" to prevent a US recession this year and especially next year, highlighting \"significant adverse risks\".",
        "\"Based on the policy outline set out at the June FOMC (Federal Open Market Committee) meeting and the expected reduction in the fiscal deficit, we expect the US economy to slow down,\" IMF Managing Director Crystalina Georgieva told a news conference.",
        "With inflation and an extremely tight labor market above the Fed's long-term target, the Fed raised the target range for the Fed at the Fed Fund rate in each of the last three meetings. Last week, the Federal Reserve raised interest rates by 75 basis points, marking the sharpest rise in interest rates since 1994.",
        "Georgieva said the IMF believes the road to a policy rate set by the Federal Reserve to get the federal funds rate from 3.5% to 4% sooner is the right policy to bring down inflation, but could cause \"some pain\" for consumers.",
        "The IMF chief also said that the IMF was aware of the risks to the US economy. \"We really see very significant disadvantages this year and especially next year,\" she said.",
        "The IMF chief's statement comes amid growing concern among a number of economists and analysts that rising inflation could push the U.S. economy into recession.",
        "According to a recent survey by economists in the Wall Street Journal, the likelihood of a recession has increased dramatically from 28% in April to 44% in the next 12 months. The latest statistics show that the data are usually only on or near the edge of the actual recession.",
        "Also, Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell said earlier this week that the Fed's aggressive rate hike could plunge the U.S. economy into recession. \"It's not our expected outcome at all, but it's definitely a risk,\" Powell told lawmakers at a congressional hearing.",
        "Meanwhile, Bill Dudley, former chairman of the Federal Reserve Bank of New York, said in a recent statement on Bloomberg that a recession is \"inevitable\" over the next 12 to 18 months.",
        "Speaking to the IMF virtual media, Nigel Choke, deputy director of the IMF's Western Hemisphere Department, said that if a recession finally occurs, it will be relatively short-lived and unemployment will rise relatively steadily."
      ],
